		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Smart guy, that Gandalf</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.33)</font> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23193">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9078">Steven "Caedmon" Alwine</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9078&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Gandalf&#39;s Wisdom denies the pool while Sauron Corruption to Beatdown wails on the opposing fellowship.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> May 6, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Starting:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(173)">Frodo, Old Bilbo&#39;s Heir</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(182)">The One Ring, The Ruling Ring</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(35)">Gimli, Son of Gloin</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(193)">Sam, Son of Hamfast</a><br>
<br>
Adventure Path:<br>
1. <a href="javascript:card_browser(205)">The Prancing Pony</a><br>
2. <a href="javascript:card_browser(214)">Trollshaw Forest</a><br>
3. <a href="javascript:card_browser(221)">Rivendell Waterfall</a><br>
4. Darrowdelf Chamber<br>
5. Bridge of Khazad-Dum<br>
6. Valley of the Silverlode<br>
7. <a href="javascript:card_browser(232)">Anduin Confluence</a><br>
8. <a href="javascript:card_browser(238)">Shores of Nen Hithoel</a><br>
9. <a href="javascript:card_browser(243)">Tol Brandir</a><br>
<br>
Free People:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(299)">Aragorn, Ranger of the North</a> x3<br>
Gandalf&#39;s Wisdom x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(304)">Athelas</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(11)">Ranger&#39;s Sword</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(301)">Aragorn&#39;s Bow</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(45)">Gimli&#39;s Battle Axe</a> x2<br>
Hand Axe x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(55)">Gimli&#39;s Helm</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(194)">Sting</a><br>
Mithril Coat<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(16)">Valiant Man of the West</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(179)">Hobbit Stealth</a> x2<br>
Flurry of Blows x4<br>
Total: 33<br>
<br>
Shadow:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(125)">Ulaire Enquea, Lieutenant of Morgul</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(128)">Ulaire Toldea, Messenger of Morgul</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(147)">Morgul Warden</a> x3<br>
Orc Scout x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(319)">Orc Ambusher</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(133)">Band of the Eye</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(149)">Orc Assassin</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(144)">Morgul Hunter</a><br>
Tower Assassin<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(163)">Thin and Stretched</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(135)">Desperate Defense of the Ring</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(867)">Enduring Evil</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(137)">Enheartened Foe</a> x2<br>
Total: 33    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> I think the Adventure path explains itself, so I&#39;m going to skip past explaining each and every site. Three Aragorns are in case the Prancing Pony isn&#39;t site 1. It&#39;s fairly plain, but the basic principle is to drop 2 Gandalf&#39;s Wisdoms, play Athelas for free whenever necessary, deck out Gimli, make the Balrog your b!+$h with Flurry of Blows and use Valiant Man when you need to beat the Swarms, or at least suck it up pretty well from the Swarms. Double tap at least once, and bid aggressively to go first, using Sam to whisk away all those excess burdens. Moving twice is a good idea, simply because forcing your opponent to keep up is all the better for your Shadow side. Moving inevitably taxes archery, especially aimed archery, which means they will have to fight, and when they have to fight, they&#39;ll add burdens thanks to Desperate Defenses. Let me say a couple things: I do not play Hates or Orc Bowmen because this deck thrives on combat, with Enduring Evils and Enheartened Foes. Forcing your opponent to fight a Band of the Eye (Quite possibly the best non-unique minion in the game) twice after you&#39;ve depleted his hand with even one Enduring Evil is a nasty combo. The Orc assassins are there to do everything possible to take out Sam. Kill Sam, and you will almost certainly win the game somewhere around site 7 or 8. Aragorn will be curbstomped by a Morgul Warden thanks to Enduring Evil. Enduring Evil kills companions, as does Enquea. Toldea just kills Sam and Legolas, but that&#39;s ok. Enjoy the deck! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23193"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23193" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
